Description:

Fantastic facilities, great staff, and the mens team in full effect!  Highlights from the sprint and gym training with an introduction by Performance Director Gary Anderson.

All the guys have an impressive background of achievement, from Craig Pickering and Joel Fearon who compete at 100m sprint, to John Jackson - a Royal Marine Physical Instructor.

Title: b'NY Football Team On Bull Strength'
Description:
b"**Sign Up For Joe's FREE Newsletter: http://synergy-athletics.com/bonus/youtube.html

 GET YOUR BULL STRENGTH: http://www.bullstrength.com ORIGINAL POST: http://synergy-athletics.com/effective-strength-training/ny-football-team-on-bull-strength/


Great news, an entire high school football team has joined my athletes in training with us at the new gym.  The best part is they are extremely dedicated.  Their coaches come to every workout and provide excellent support as their athletes get stronger quickly!

Here is a glimpse at their program.
Monday's Workout

1.  Bench Press 5 x 2
2a.  Close Grip Bench 4 x 5
3b.  Thick Grip Supine Rows 4 x 12 (hockey puck bar)
4a.  One Arm Military 4 x 8
5b. Dumbbell Windmills 4 x 8

Finisher:  Plate Stack Walks (I meant to get a video out of this, it's awesome biceps, shoulders and core)

With large groups we break up the finishers and the accessory works based on needs and abilities.  In the strength workout video below you will see thick rope hand over hand sled pulls and a few other exercises worked in.  

- Joe Hashey, CSCS -

Title: b'Musculation Avant/Apr\xc3\xa8s'
b"Jason Wheat's Big And Strong MVP Chest Workout - Bodybuilding.com"
Description:
b"Building a big, strong chest should be at the top of every MVP's to-do list. Jason Wheat's compound-based, pyramid-driven chest workout will help you get the job done.

Follow Jason's Full Routine Here: http://bbcom.me/1FFRvP1

In pursuit of bigger pecs, most gym-goers slide under the bar every Monday to celebrate International Chest Day. They knock out a few sets of bench presses for 10-12 reps, play around with a few more accessory movements, and call it a day. Don't get me wrong: training like this to build a big chest is fine, but it's not enough to qualify you for MVP status.

In my book, an MVP is someone who trains for more than aesthetics. Man or woman, an MVP trains to look good, build strength, and perform well. An MVP wants to push the boundaries of every category on every body part and turn every workout into a challenge, not a walk in the park. Put simply, an MVP wants to build a chest that's big and strong.

With that in mind, the goal of this chest workout is to help you build size and strength simultaneously. Throw this sucker into your split and your body will get better at working under a heavy load. Heavier weights will allow you to do more damage, see more growth, and put up even bigger numbers in the gym over time.

If you're used to doing 3 sets of 10-12 reps, this workout could throw you for a loop. You're going to be working for fewer reps, but you'll be putting a lot more weight on the bar. You'll still get the blood pumping and build mass, but you'll get the added benefit of increased strength."

Title: b'Bicep Workout - Best Bicep Workout For Mass'
Description:
b"Bicep workout Best Bicep Workout For Mass 

Hey guys, thanks for watching! Please leave a comment & thumbs up, & subscribe for more videos on bicep workout 

Please subscribe for more news on bicep workout and workouts: http://www.youtube.com/user/healthandfitnessnews

In every gym that you go to, you will see people pumping their biceps. Biceps along with the pecs and abs are sometimes called vanity muscles because they are the most visible and therefore commands the most respect. Invariably, when you ask someone to show you his muscles, he will probably flex his biceps.

Before we discuss biceps development, I want to point out that the biceps make up only one third of your upper arm with triceps the other two-thirds. So to have an impressive arm, you must build your triceps too or the effort on your biceps will not show good results. Many people fail to realize this and that is why you see them doing curls after curls without much improvement. We will touch on triceps exercises in another article. For now, let's talk about biceps.

Here are some exercises that will blast your biceps. Most of you would have done some or all of these exercises. The question I am asking is, are the exercises done in the correct form and techniques because if they are not, you will most likely be wasting your time as your biceps will not grow to its full potential. Perform each exercise for 3-5 sets once or twice a week and at reps between 6-10, but make sure that at the high end of the reps, you will not be so fatigued that you can't perform another rep in good form. 

a) Standing Barbell Curl/ EZY Bar 

You can perform this exercise with either a straight bar or an ezy bar. This is a great mass building exercises for your biceps. Stand with feet shoulder width apart and grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands should also be about shoulder width apart. Curl the bar up slowly focusing intensely on the biceps contraction. Do not swing or use momentum to curl especially at the later stages when your biceps get weaker. Never swing or move your body, only your arms are moving. Keep your elbows locked to the side of your body and do not pivot them.Then lower the weight, taking 3-4 seconds resisting the weight on the way down to emphasize the negative part of the exercise. Never let gravity pull the weights down. At all times, do not curl or bend your wrist which must always be in a straight neutral position. 

b) Incline Dumbbell Curls 

This exercise will hit different fibre in your biceps and gives you the peak bicep look.
Sit back on an incline bench holding a dumbbell in each hand, keep your elbows well forward throughout the movement, curl the weight upward and toward the shoulder level. Then squeeze your biceps hard at the top position. Lower the weights again, slowly under full control. The speed and techniques are similar to what was described earlier. 

Please subscribe for more news on bicep workout and workouts: http://www.youtube.com/user/healthandfitnessnews

c) Preacher Curl 

Similar to barbell curl but using the preacher curl station. 
This is an excellent bicep peaking isolation exercise.

d) Hammer Curl 

Hammer curl gives your biceps the full look and your forearms are also working hard.
Similar to incline dumbbell curl except you will be using the hammer grip on the dumbbell like holding a hammer knocking nails in and standing up instead of sitting down. 

e) Build Biceps Tips 

Focus on the movement of your biceps all throughout the motion. Don't lift weights that are too heavy that will compromise your form and techniques to show off. By slightly turning and squeezing, you'll build more peak on your biceps. Like all exercises, pose and stretch the biceps between sets. This is to flush out lactic acid and help your biceps recover better for the next set. Remember to change the order of the exercises you perform after 6-8 weeks to shock your biceps into new growth and watch those arms grow!

Please subscribe for more news on bicep workout and workouts: http://www.youtube.com/user/healthandfitnessnews

Title: b'Aumentare Massa Muscolare: Principio dello Stripping'
Description:
b'SCOPRI COME POSSO AIUTARTI A DISTANZA:  goo.gl/VjJM5g

Scopri in questo video il Principio dello Stripping

Lo stripping o drop set (detto anche serie discendente o serie a scalare) \xc3\xa8 una tecnica speciale ad alta intensit\xc3\xa0 (HITM) applicata nell'esercizio coi pesi, in particolare nel body building e fitness.

Esistono alcuni nomi alternativi che vengono utilizzati solo in alcune varianti: Triple drop set \xc3\xa8 quando il carico viene scalato per 2 volte, e quindi vengono adoperati 3 differenti carichi; Double drop set \xc3\xa8 quando il carico viene scalato per a volta, adoperando 2 differenti carichi. Down the rack o Running the rack possono essere terminologie usate quando questa tecnica prevede l'uso dei manubri

Title: b'Caffeine - Before Your Workout - Lee Labrada'
Description:
b"Lee Labrada Explains Caffeine 
 == FREE 12 WEEK PHYSIQUE TRANSFORMATION PROGRAM :http://www.labrada.com/12weekleanbody 

SUPERCHARGE - as shown in video - http://www.labrada.com/store/SC_Xtreme.html 

Please feel free to ask any questions you may have regarding Fitness or Nutrition and I will be happy to try and answer them. Here's where you can ask.. http://www.labrada.com/asklee

This week's question comes from John Dickinson, McKinney, Texas. 

QUESTION: Do you think consuming caffeine before a workout is beneficial?

ANSWER: John, I've always thought that caffeine before my workout is beneficial. My personal observation is that it helps me to stay more focused and more energized.

Studies show that caffeine helps athletes exercise faster and with more force, over longer periods of time. Caffeine is so effective at increasing exercise performance that until recently it was banned by the World Anti-Doping Agency.

Caffeine increases exercise endurance by helping muscles use more blood sugar. One study shows that caffeine increases the entry of sugar into muscles by as much as 26 percent.

Of course you have to have enough blood sugar for the caffeine to work with, so you would preferably consume your caffeine with a pre-workout carbohydrate drink or snack.

Caffeine helps the brain fire into nerves to cause a greater percentage of muscle fibers to contract at the same time. This is one of the key benefits during weight training, because if you can recruit more muscle fibers more efficiently you have greater contractions, and hence greater results.

So how much caffeine should you use?

One study shows that a caffeine dose of 3 mg/kg body weight improves cycling performance in well-trained athletes. That comes to a little more than 300 mg for a 220 lb. athlete prior to or during a competition.

Caffeine is thought to lose its performance enhancing beneficial effects with repeated exposure, so athletes who want to gain maximum advantage from caffeine will want to cycle on and off during the year.

BTW, you can get 300 mg of caffeine from a tall cup of Starbucks coffee. 
Or, you can do what I do and get 450 mg of caffeine from two scoops of our Super Charge! Xtreme4.0, along with 9 other must-have performance-enhancing supplements that will help take your workouts to new levels. 

Give it a try, see what you think. John, I hope that helps.

Title: b'Como Tonificar los Abdominales, Abdominales Rapidos, Ejercicios Para Quemar Grasa'
Description:
b'Clic aqu\xc3\xad: http://tinyurl.com/absperfecto

Conseguir unos abdominales marcados es el gran objeto de deseo de la mayor\xc3\xada de los hombres, Para tener unos buenos abdominales es necesario combinar tres tipos de trabajo: tonificaci\xc3\xb3n, ejercicio aer\xc3\xb3bico y control nutricional,El ejercicio aer\xc3\xb3bico es fundamental para conseguir una zona abdominal definida, ya que por muchos abdominales que hagamos, nunca se nos marcar\xc3\xa1n si no quemamos la grasa que los recubre.

"A la hora de entrenar los abdominales se cometen muchos errores, como olvidar el trabajo de la zona lumbar, fundamental para compensar muscularmente el cuerpo y evitar molestias y dolores de espalda, como el cl\xc3\xa1sico lumbago.

Entrenar la zona abdominal no es s\xc3\xb3lo cuesti\xc3\xb3n de est\xc3\xa9tica, Tener unos abdominales fuertes y con buen tono muscular, junto con la zona lumbar, nos ayudar\xc3\xa1 a fijar y estabilizar la columna vertebral.

Adem\xc3\xa1s del entrenamiento f\xc3\xadsico hay que seguir un peque\xc3\xb1o plan nutrici\xc3\xb3n para ayudar a eliminar la grasa en la zona y marcar los m\xc3\xbasculos abdominales.

Tonificar y quemar.

El trabajo abdominal requiere un orden de trabajo justificado. Empezamos por la zona inferior del abdomen, ya que es la m\xc3\xa1s d\xc3\xa9bil; luego har\xc3\xadamos los abdominales oblicuos y terminar\xc3\xadamos con la zona superior del abdomen, que es la parte m\xc3\xa1s fuerte, Seguir este orden de trabajo te ayudar\xc3\xa1 a aguantar bien las repeticiones, ya que comenzar por los superiores har\xc3\xada que te cansases antes.

Adem\xc3\xa1s, la importancia de la respiraci\xc3\xb3n en el trabajo abdominal, ya que potencia el trabajo en conjunto y la tonificaci\xc3\xb3n del recto abdominal. Hay que inspirar cuando el abdominal est\xc3\xa9 en extensi\xc3\xb3n y expulsar el aire al hacer flexi\xc3\xb3n del m\xc3\xbasculo.

Al trabajo espec\xc3\xadfico de tonificaci\xc3\xb3n hay que a\xc3\xb1adirle ejercicio aer\xc3\xb3bico (correr, montar en bici, hacer spinning, m\xc3\xa1quina el\xc3\xadptica) para quemar la grasa acumulada en el abdomen, La intensidad y frecuencia de este trabajo aer\xc3\xb3bico depender\xc3\xa1 de nuestro estado de forma f\xc3\xadsica. Intensificar el entrenamiento aer\xc3\xb3bico tambi\xc3\xa9n nos ayudar\xc3\xa1 a definir m\xc3\xa1s los abdominales, lo que, combinado con un buen trabajo de tonificaci\xc3\xb3n, nos ayudar\xc3\xa1 a conseguir un abdomen definido.

Title: b'Why in the heck am I doing Body Beast?!?'
Description:
b'Why in the heck is a 41-year-old mom of two boys doing Body Beast? Great question...it took me a while to get to an answer. You see, my adult life I've been fascinated with weight lifting, body building, and watching people change their shape. Since I found Beachbody in 2005, I've learned to push myself and see what I'm made of--time and again. After doing P90X, then ChaLEAN Extreme, then Turbo Fire (as well as "dabbling in countless other programs along the way) one thing I know for sure: I can do more than I ever thought I could. 

I'm good at self-doubt. An expert self-loather. That said, really getting serious about ME (both my mental and physical health) opened a LOT of doors in my mind. Whereas before the space in my brain was pretty dark--I've learned that

I'm in control of that and can let some light in. Gradually over time, I've pushed myself out of my comfort zone time and time and time and time again and live in a much sunnier space. These slight shifts--subtle changes over time--have given me a new spirit. A confidence I've never had before. Will I blow you away with my results? I dunno. But I'm gonna blow myself away with my efforts. 

My biggest pending challenge will NOT be tossing around the weights. It's going to be eating enough clean fuel to promote the muscle growth. On that note (ladies), muscle burns more calories while you're sitting at your PC reading this blog. We (especially women 30 and older) need muscle. Our metabolism doesn't slow down cuz we are old--it slows down cuz we lose that glorious muscle we had in our youth. Want to fire that metabolism up again? Pick up a weight. A heavy one. Repeatedly. Anyhoo--I'm a lifelong meal skipper. It's been one of my greatest challenges...eating enough calories. So, I'm expecting this to challenge me. I've got to hit around 3,000 calories a day according to the book--double what I typically eat. It's a good thing I LOVE the menus in that book! They're amazing! 

Oh please...do not believe that myth that skipping meals helps you lose weight. lt doens't. Skipping meals freaks your body out. It thinks you're in Alaska in the peak of snow season stuck on the side of a road with no hope of eating again. Your body instinctively goes into survival mode and starts eating muscle--storing the fat so you can handle the sub zero temps while you run from the Yeti. That gorgeous lean smooth muscle--and your body canibilzes on it; saving the ugly dimply squishy fat for later. Yeah, I'll wait for you if you want to go grab a snack and come back to me.

Oh, and another thing...I don't wanna get all manly, either. 

Follow along. Should be one heckuva ride!

http://www.Commitment2Fitness.com'

Title: b'Killer Fat-Loss Training in One Set - 100 reps of 1 Arm Gripping DB Squats'
Description:
b"http://www.metabolicsurgerapidfatloss.com

So if I were given an ultimatum and told I could only do one set of one exercise and that would be all I could do for a fat loss workout, THIS would it...

The One-Arm Gripping Dumbbell Squat done for a 100 rep set.

The exercise itself is awesome...

...it's essentially a dumbbell squat holding a single dumbbell in one hand while you grip onto a bar or other solid object with the other. 

This allows you to keep an upright torso position, taking all the stress off the lower back (and much of it off the knees) while you do a squat. It also focuses more of the workload onto the quads.

And because you're holding onto something with one hand, you can actually USE that other hand to spot yourself, in addition to helping keep your balance during the exercise. 

This means you involve your upper body (biceps and lats) in the squat movement, making it a total-body exercise.

Now we're going to do it for 100 reps...doing 10 reps gripping with the right, then 10 reps with the left, etc. Keep going back and forth until you hit 100 reps total.

The idea here is to crank up your Lactic Acid production in order to maximize the GH secretion your body responds with. GH is one of THE key hormones for burning fat while keeping muscle mass.

Weight selection can be a bit tricky the first time you do it...I'm using a 65 lb dumbbell for this and I got 100 reps straight through. If you start too heavy, just get as many reps as you can. Rest 10 seconds, then get as many MORE reps as you can. Rest 10 seconds, etc. Keeping that going until you hit 100 reps total.

Yes it works and yes you will hate me for it.

Enjoy ;)..."

Title: b'Protein Myth BUSTED!! (Cooked Protein and Shakes)'
Description:
b'Sacrifice nothing with your protein supplements.  Turn to what the pros use...
http://athleanx.com/x/pro-athlete-supplements

Many people think that cooking protein causes it to either lose its nutritional quality or it hinders the muscle building properties of the food.  Even more think that when choosing the right whey protein shake, you need to choose those that do not use high heat processing since it causes denaturing and renders the protein useless.  Time to debunk those big protein myths!

While heating a protein molecule will cause it to denature, all this means is that it changes the shape of the molecule without loss of it's content.  Unless of course we are talking about completely charring or destroying the protein beyond recognition, simple heat or cooking applied to a high protein food will not cause that protein to disappear.

On the other hand, the other active component of high protein foods is the bioactive allergen molecules.  These allergens are those molecules responsible for binding to our bodies own immune mediating structures...namely immunoglobulin E.  When the two bind together, your body experiences an enhanced immune response, unless you are allergic to the allergen.

Heat can cause this allergen to either become enhanced in it's effectiveness (or allergy inducing abilities) or it can cause it to be destroyed entirely.  This depends on the source of the protein.  In the case of whey protein supplements, the allergen (lactoferrin in particular) is destroyed so choosing high heat methods of whey preparation will sacrifice the immune boosting benefits.  That said, it does nothing to lower the protein content of the whey protein.

Many will ask "are whey protein supplements necessary or needed".  Lots of the confusion comes from those that are unsure of this whole protein myth in the first place.  Some will even turn to "raw protein" in favor of cooked for this same mistruth.

If you're training or working out hard, high quality whey protein has been shown to provide muscle building benefits.  Sticking to cold processed micro filtration methods will help to preserve the additional immune enhancing benefits of whey without obviously sacrificing any of the protein content (regardless of the preparation method).

If you want to get the highest quality protein supplements along with a complete protein shake recipe guide you can head to http://athleanx.com/athleanrx and get the lineup that pro athletes are turning to to build muscle and get ripped all season long...ATHLEAN-Rx.

For more videos on whey supplements and supplements to help you build muscle, be sure to head to subscribe to our channel here on youtube at http://youtube.com/user/jdcav24'

Title: b'Pilihlah Makanan Berserat'
Description:
b'Karbohidrat merupakan sumber tenaga. Makanan mengandung karbohidrat yang masuk dalam tubuh akan diubah menjadi zat gula. Hormon insulin dalam darah kemudian mengolah gula tersebut untuk disalurkan ke organ-organ tubuh seperti otot, hati, dan lemak. Gula dalam otot itulah yang menghasilkan tenaga. Namun, jika karbohidrat tak terpakai maka tersimpan sebagai lemak. Lemak yang berlebih ini yang menyebabkan seseorang kegemukan.

Dalam mengkonsumsi karbohidrat, binaragawan nasional Ade Rai menganjurkan pilih makanan berkarbohidrat dengan serat paling tinggi. Menurut Ade, serat yang tinggi untuk memperlambat gula masuk dalam darah. Alhasil, tubuh tidak mudah menyimpan karbohidrat yang telah berubah menjadi lemak.

Sumber karbohidrat paling populer adalah nasi, baik itu nasi putih maupun nasi merah. Namun, Anda sebaiknya memilih nasi merah karena berserat paling tinggi. Makanan berkarbohidrat lainnya adalah roti. Ada baiknya Anda memilih roti gandum yang mengandung serat lebih banyak. Selain itu, kentang bisa juga menjadi alternatif sumber karbohidrat. Makanan umbi-umbian ini bisa digoreng, direbus, maunpun dibakar untuk menggugah selera makan.'

Title: b'Peyow Aqua Pilates Workout Basics'

Peyow Aqua Pilates - Pilates principles adapted fpr the water. "Peyow" is the Mandarin word for "float," so "Floating Pilates."  Peyow Aqua Pilates is designed to use water's natural resistance to increase the body's full range of motion while stabilizing the core muscles.  The mind-body workout incorporates movements based on the Pilates method.  Set in the healing environment of water, the workout facilitates increased flexibility while challenging individuals to maintain core stabilization, postural alignment, and balance.  

With the use of noodles and water dumbbells, Peyow Aqua Pilates exercises are suitable for all levels of conditioning.'

Title: b"Arnold Schwarzenegger - Six Secrets Of The Oak's Success - Youtube"
Description:
b'Muscle&Strength Store is the #1 for bodybuilding supplements, fitness gear & workout accessories. Lowest Prices!
http://j.mp/MuscleAndStrengthStore



5 THINGS THAT MADE ARNOLD
1 He loved to train

Sure, the workouts we did were hard and grueling. But we also knew that training is supposed to be fun, so we made it that way. Arnold trained hard, and there were no secrets to his gains other than pounding out the sets and reps with good heavy weights. Of course we all eventually had injuries to deal with that changed the game, but in the early days, there was nothing more fun than intense, heavy training with classic movements.

2 He used variety\xe2\x80\x94but not too much

Arnold liked to vary the exercises and throw in new movements weekly to change things up, but the sets and reps usually stayed pretty consistent. The Arnold Blueprint trainer is a good representation of the sort of work he did. Nevertheless, he knew that there were some movements that always needed to be a priority. For instance, we would occasionally compete in bench press, primarily because Arnold was so competitive and I always had a slight edge on that lift. My best was 455 pounds, and I think his was around 440.

3 He liked old-fashioned cardio

Today, it seems like nearly everybody in the weight room has built a wall around themselves in the form of a pair of headphones. This is even more the case when it comes to cardio, where you watch TV while you work the treadmill or bike. Talk about solitary confinement! Back in our day, there were none of these machines, and "cardio" was a run on the beach. It was fun, social, and as Arnold has said recently, it was the best way to build a tan that didn't suck.


4 He relied on proven nutrition principles

When we were training at our peak, supplements were pretty limited. Sure, we had protein at times, but that was about as far as it went, so most of what we built was powered by eating real food\xe2\x80\x94and good food. I'm talking about high protein, high fat, and limited carbs, like nutrition experts are starting to advocate more and more these days. Funny how it all comes around. 



5 He learned from his training

People talk about someone having a "winning personality," but until they've met Arnold, they've never really seen it in its purest form. He approached every situation with the expectation that he would get what he wanted, both inside the gym and out.

He trained hard, ate right, and saw his future place in a bigger picture. He knew discipline was the key if the end result was going to be good. He paid his dues overcoming a language barrier, becoming a United States citizen, and learning his way in a new country. From the start, the gym was his home base and most comfortable environment. Once he found his way there, he attacked everything else in his life in the same way.'

Video Summary:

Build Bigger Arms With The "Reverse Cable Curl"

In this post I want to share a fairly uncommon arm exercise that you can use to build bigger arms and pack on more overall muscle size: the reverse grip cable curl.

This movement is just like a regular bicep curl, but as the name implies, you'll grip the bar with your palms facing down rather than up. This position shifts more stress onto the brachialis (a muscle on the side of the arm between the bicep and tricep) and the brachioradialis (the top of your forearm) to help you build arm mass more effectively. If you want to get the best arm workouts possible, you can try including this in your plan from time to time.

Here's how to go about performing these in order to get bigger arms as efficiently as possible..

Proper Reverse Cable Curl Form:

- Simply set the cable as low on the machine as it will go and use a regular straight bar attachment. 

- Grip the bar with your palms facing down and cock your wrists slightly.

- Perform a regular curl while keeping your shoulders down and back and elbows tucked at your sides.

You can perform your reverse grip curls for 2-4 sets using 8-10 reps. Include these in your bicep workout at the very end after all of your bicep work is done. 

Again, these are a fairly uncommon arm exercise but help to hit the muscles from a slightly different angle in order to help you gain arm mass in a way that you may not get from performing standard bicep curls only.

Give these a try and see what you think. They can be performed 1-2 times per week, and just like any other arm exercise, focus on progressive overload by adding more resistance over time.'

Title: b'Leg Training Exercises - Advanced Unilateral Movements'
Description:
b"**Sign Up For Joe's FREE Newsletter: http://synergy-athletics.com/bonus/youtube.html

 Lunge to step up and Split squat to RDL.  ORIGINAL POST:  http://synergy-athletics.com/?p=2891 HUGE WORKOUTS http://www.bullstrength.com 

Standard unilateral exercises: Front lunge, Back lunge, Step up, Split squat, Sprinting,Side lunges, Sled dragging, Single leg RDL, Pistol squats

Advanced Unilateral Leg Exercises:
I have had good success with increasing time under tension and/or shifting the bodyweight during the movement.   For example, during a regular front lunge, the person steps out and then drives back.  There is no shifting of the weight completely to the front leg.

Instead, here are some advanced variations that will really take your unilateral training to the next level!  Some of these are unique to Synergy Athletics - so I hope that you can benefit from the information.

 Walking lunge, Reverse Lunge with front foot elevated, Lunge to step up, Zercher Lunge, 
Step up / RDL combo, Split squat with added ROM (front foot on a short box), 
Split squat to RDL.


- Joe Hashey, CSCS -

Title: b'Campionati Europei Under 17 Bucarest 2012 - Il trionfo di Mirco Scarantino'
Description: b"Mirco Scarantino trionfa nella categoria maschile fino a 56 kg aggiudicandosi cos\xc3\xac il secondo titolo Europeo Under 17 consecutivo. Neanche il cambio di categoria ha impedito al nisseno figlio d'arte di confermarsi ai vertici della Pesistica Europea: lo scorso anno in Polonia si impose su tutti nella 50 kg, quest'anno, a Bucarest, nella 56 kg.\nNonostante al termine della prova di strappo, con il risultato di 100 kg, si trovasse alle spalle di due avversari, l'armeno Saribekyan (103 kg) e il russo Konoplev (101 kg), nell'esercizio di slancio ha dominato i rivali sollevando in prima prova 123 kg e in seconda 130 kg, rinunciando poi all'ultimo tentativo divenuto inutile alla luce dei 15 kg di differenza tra lui e il rivale pi\xc3\xb9 pericoloso per la classifica del totale, il pesista armeno."

Title: b'4 Causes of UNEVEN MUSCLES (and how YOU can FIX them!)'
Description:
b'Muscle imbalances holding back your muscle size and strength?  Fix them here...
http://athleanx.com/x/fixyourmuscles

Muscle imbalances and uneven muscle development can impact the strength, endurance and shape.  Most often, the wrong workout program is to blame, since it pushes you to do too many reps of the wrong exercises, which creates this uneven shift.  

To fix your uneven muscles you have to first identify what type of muscle imbalance you have.  Is it a strength imbalance?  Is one arm bigger than the other?  Is one pec bigger than the other?  Is your overall muscle size just flat out uneven?  Do you fatigue on one side faster than the other?

All of these are quite common, but they are all fixable or at least able to be improved greatly.

I present techniques that you can use in each one of the circumstances that I just mentioned above.  We cover neurologic strength reasons for left vs right side discrepancies, circulatory reasons for faster fatigue right vs left, coordination and joint mechanics, and finally genetics.

That said, if you are still using the wrong workout program (one that hasn't been created by a sports medicine professional with a physical therapy background - yes...those fitness "gurus" reading a few magazines doesn't count) then you are eventually going to regenerate the same muscle imbalances and asymmetry.

It's time to fix those forever.  If you haven't already joined TEAM ATHLEAN, then it's time you do.  Head to http://athleanx.com/x/fixyourmuscles and see what it's like to overlook nothing in your workouts and to start training like an athlete.

For more workout videos and exercises on how to correct uneven muscles as well as videos on supplementation, workout advice and nutrition - be sure to subscribe to our channel on youtube at http://youtube.com/user/jdcav24'

Viele Fitness-Sportler denken direkt ans Bankdr\xc3\xbccken, wenn sie das Wort 'Brustmuskeltraining' h\xc3\xb6ren. Dabei gibt es f\xc3\xbcr die Brust weitere gute M\xc3\xb6glichkeiten neue Wachstumsreize zu setzen. Eine gute Muskelaufbau-\xc3\x9cbung sind tiefe Dips mit Zusatzgewicht.

F\xc3\xbcr dieses Muskelaufbau-Training brauchst Du eine Dips-Vorrichtung, welche sich in jedem guten Fitness-Studio finden l\xc3\xa4sst. Damit das Brust-Training richtig intensiv wird, solltest Du dir eine Kurzhantel als Zusatzgewicht zwischen deine Beine einklemmen. Deine Arme sollten bei dieser Brust-\xc3\x9cbung weit nach au\xc3\x9fen gehen und dein Oberk\xc3\xb6rper sollte nach vorne gebeugt sein. Mach so viele Wiederholungen wie Du mit dem Zusatzgewicht schaffst. Dann legst Du die Kurzhantel beiseite und gehst wiederum bis zum Muskelversagen. Als weitere Intensit\xc3\xa4tstechnik kannst Du in die Ausgangsposition der Dips springen und dann dein K\xc3\xb6rper langsam nach unten ablassen. 

Bau dieses Brusttraining mit Dips in deinen Trainingsplan f\xc3\xbcr den Oberk\xc3\xb6rper ein. Du wirst dadurch einen extremem Muskelpump in der Brust bekommen und einen zus\xc3\xa4tzlichen Reiz f\xc3\xbcr neues Muskelwachstum und eine gr\xc3\xb6\xc3\x9fere Brust setzen. Mit diesem Workout ist der Muskelaufbau garantiert!

Weitere n\xc3\xbctzliche Trainingstips findest Du auf meinem Youtube-Kanal. Abonniere ihn am besten gleich - somit bleibst Du immer auf dem Laufenden. F\xc3\xbcr Fragen und Antworten besucht Du mich auf meiner Facebook-Seite unter http://www.facebook.com/esskarl

... und auf meiner eigenen Website http://www.KARL-ESS.com gibt's jede Menge Infos rund um Fitness, Ern\xc3\xa4hrung und Gesundheit.

Title: b'Cardio on an Empty Stomach (good or bad)'
Description:
b"Does doing cardio on an empty stomach burn more bodyfat? Watch the video to find out...

FREE 12 week workout program: http://full.sc/19cNIdo 
Like my Facebook Page: http://full.sc/1f2etSa
Follow me on Twitter: http://full.sc/19cNoLN

When training for fat loss should you do cardio in the morning before eating breakfast? There are different schools of thought on this subject, but the main thing when it comes to doing cardio for fat loss is that you simply do it.

Cardio done at anytime of day is better than no cardio at all. And weight training done at any time of day is better than no weight training at all. So before you get hung up on when you do your cardio and weight training workouts, make sure you are doing them consistently first.

As for doing early morning cardio on an empty stomach, there are pros and cons to this practice. 

Some of the pros is that you'll be able to tap into burning stored bodyfat for fuel easier when your glycogen levels are low from an overnight fast.

Another benefit is that you'll get your cardio workout done and out of the way first thing in the morning. A lot of times guys get lazy when it comes to cardio and may blow off the cardio workout if they wait until later in the day. But if you do it first thing in the morning you won't get distracted by other things.

Some of the cons to doing cardio first thing in the morning is that you won't have the same strength and energy as you would if you did cardio with food in your system. 

This is important if you are doing cardio for athletic performance. But for fat loss it really doesn't make that big of a difference because generally you'll only be doing lower intensity longer duration cardio first thing in the morning.

I would not recommend doing a high intensity cardio workout first thing in the morning as this will be too intense and you won't have the energy to give it 100% when running on empty.

When it comes to weight training workouts you should NOT lift weights on an empty stomach. The reason for this is that weight training is a high intensity performance exercise. You can't simply go through the motions with weight training like you can with cardio.

Your weight training should be intense and progressive. For this reason I'd recommend having at least 1 or 2 meals in your system before hitting the gym for weight lifting. You'll feel stronger and make better gains when you have some food in your system."

Title: b'Rutina Para Gluteos. Rutina Para Desarrollar Gluteos'
Description:
b'Clic aqu\xc3\xad: http://Tr4iner.com
Es hora de lograr el cuerpo de tus sue\xc3\xb1os!


Hoy les tenemos una rutina para desarrollar tus gluteos, un tema que tantas veces me preguntaron y el d\xc3\xada de hoy en este video te voy a ense\xc3\xb1ar una rutina detallada para gl\xc3\xbateos.  

El primer ejercicio van a ser las sentadillas. Con la barra colocaba bien en tus trapecios, te posicionas bien y sacas la barra del rack, espalda recta todo el tiempo eso es fundamental que lo tengas presente, inspiras profundamente al inicio y bajas.

El segundo ejercicio que vas hacer en esta rutina de gluteos son los step ups. Colocas una pierna adelante sobre el banco y la otra lo m\xc3\xa1s pegado posible al banco, cuanto m\xc3\xa1s elevado sea el banco mayor dificultad por tanto debes encontrar un banco que se acople a tu nivel y en base a eso progresivamente puedes ir buscando un banco m\xc3\xa1s elevado. La ejecuci\xc3\xb3n es la siguiente: debes intentar que la pierna que est\xc3\xa1 adelante sea la que haga todo el esfuerzo, al inicio quiz\xc3\xa1s hasta que te vayas acostumbrando un poco te vas a apoyar en la pierna de atr\xc3\xa1s pero intenta como te dec\xc3\xada que el movimiento sea m\xc3\xa1s que todo con la pierna que est\xc3\xa1 delante. Mant\xc3\xa9n la espalda recta todo el tiempo, las manos pueden ir a los costados o adelante como mejor te parezca, no hay ninguna regla al respecto pues el movimiento en s\xc3\xad est\xc3\xa1 en la pierna que est\xc3\xa1 sobre el banco. Una vez terminas todas las repeticiones respectivas con una pierna inmediatamente pasas a hacer con la otra.

Y para finalizar esta rutina haremos las extensiones de cadera en maquina. Espalda recta, tus manos bien firmes agarrando el sujetador de la maquina, aprietas el gl\xc3\xbateo que est\xc3\xa1 trabajando, elevas hasta lo m\xc3\xa1s arriba que puedas. Para mantener una constante tensi\xc3\xb3n en tus gluteos no choques el disco con el otro disco. Es fundamental que sientas que el gl\xc3\xbateo est\xc3\xa9 trabajando pues si no sientes entonces no vas a obtener los resultados que tanto deseas. Una vez que termines de hacer las repeticiones con una pierna pasas hacer con la otra y vas a hacer el mismo movimiento.

=================================
Rutina Para Gluteos

-Ejercicio 1: Sentadillas
4 series de 8-10 repeticiones

-Ejercicio 2: Step ups
4 series de 8-10 repeticiones (por pierna)

-Ejercicio 3: Extensiones de cadera en maquina
4 series de 12-15 repeticiones (por pierna)

DESCANSO ENTRE SERIES: 1 minuto

=================================

Title: b'Tenn Vols Strength Training Complex'
Description: b'http://www.athleticstrengthandpower.com/\nThey\'re  the same iconic checkerboard endzones emblazoned upon the football fields in Knoxville, Tennessee...home of the University of Tennessee Vols. Yet, they\'re cast under a new light since Head Football Coach Butch Jones has come to town. The new staff has embraced the Tennessee Volunteer past by opening their arms and facilities to the former players and lettermen who paved the way for one of the top winningest programs in all of college football. \n There have been no games yet, but there\'s been plenty of winter strength training, high energy conditioning sessions and spring football. Spirits are high and for the new coaches, the whirlwind has yet to really slow down. But, that makes little difference to the Vols Football Director of Strength and Conditioning. Coach Dave Lawson knows all about the demands and high expectations of what Tennessee Football is all about. The mantra in Knoxville is basically... "we just wanna win." Lawson and his cohort, Assistant Strength & Conditioning Coach Mike Szerszen, rolled up their sleeves when they arrived at their new $50,000,000 Vols Football training complex.... and it\'s been go-go-go ever since!  So take a look at the photos and video from the Hammer Strength Clinic 2013 from Knoxville, Tennessee. This is truly one of the most impressive training centers that you\'ll find anywhere.'

Title: b'Bicep Workout, The Wrong Way & The Right Way'
Description:
b'The Bicep Workout that worked for me.

http://www.facebook.com/howigotabs - like my fan page on Facebook

http://www.howigotabs.com - Get your free 6 pack abs getting course

I was in the gym yesterday and noticed a lot of guys doing a bicep curl the absolute wrong way.

In this video I will show you the right way and the wrong way.

I'm not saying that this is the best bicep workout. In my experience there is no best workout. You simply need to find a workout that has worked for many others then test it on your own body. 

You should track everything you do from how often you workout, how much weight you're lifting to how many reps and sets you're doing.

I like to do very controlled motion bicep workouts. I see a lot of guys in the gym doing this rocking motion (sometimes referred to as putting English). 

One of my favorite bicep workouts is to use the "preacher" bench. It forces you to NOT rock back and forth and puts all the focus on your Bicep muscles.

I like to use a straight bar, ez-bar, and single dumbell curls on the preacher bench.

If you want build your biceps or  grow the muscle then be sure to watch this video about doing bicep curls with dumbbells!

Link on youtube to the bicep workout video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y4lVPc3wYVc'

Title: b'Curso de Pilates: Clases de Pilates by ORTHOS'
Description:
b'En este bonito spot, con m\xc3\xbasica cl\xc3\xa1sica; nuestra profesora de Pilates en ORTHOS Barcelona -Francesca Garcia- y Tobias K\xc3\xbchn, muestran diferentes posturas, ejercicos y posiciones de Studio Pilates con el Reformer.

Si quieres consultar informaci\xc3\xb3n sobre nuestros cursos de Pilates, te mostramos adjuntos los enlaces correspondientes:

\xc2\xb7 Curso STUDIO PILATES: http://goo.gl/qEdi2m

\xc2\xb7 Curso de MAT PILATES: http://goo.gl/U45Jkg

Puedes consultar m\xc3\xa1s art\xc3\xadculos escritos por Francesca Garcia en nuestro blog: http://fitnessyterapias.es/cesca-garcia/

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A continuaci\xc3\xb3n os adjuntamos un texto de la profesora de Pilates en ORTHOS Barcelona -PMA Teacher acreditada por la Pilates Method Alliance: (http://www.pilatesmethodalliance.org)- 

El entrenamiento originario que dise\xc3\xb1\xc3\xb3 Joseph Pilates constaba de una serie de ejercicios, de los cuales unos se realizaban sin ning\xc3\xban tipo de maquinaria, MAT, y otros con maquinaria. Este segundo recibe el nombre actualmente el nombre de ESTUDIO PILATES.
Este Estudio Pilates consta de diversas m\xc3\xa1quinas: Reformer, Cadillac, Wunda Chair, Ladder Barrel, Spine Corrector y el Ped- o- Pull.
Este entrenamiento de Pilates mediante maquinarias, comparte con el MAT, la \xe2\x80\x9cEsencia\xe2\x80\x9d, es decir, los principios de Pilates, los conceptos esenciales y todos aquellos otros conceptos ligados al 100% con este entrenamiento, como la cocontracci\xc3\xb3n de los m\xc3\xbasculos de una misma zona o el concepto del alargamiento en oposici\xc3\xb3n. Pero son un sinf\xc3\xadn de ejercicios y movimientos que observados desde fuera poco o nada se pueden parecer a los de MAT.
El estudio Pilates que os mostramos en esta grabaci\xc3\xb3n, est\xc3\xa1 dise\xc3\xb1ado para ejecutar en entrenamiento personal o en semigrupales, ya que dada su dificultad t\xc3\xa9cnica es necesario un feedback constante por parte del entrenador al cliente. No obstante, los ejercicios de Pilates adaptados para principiantes o adaptados por el personal correspondiente pueden ser excelentes ejercicios rehabilitadores, reeducadores y facilitadores.  

El Reformer, es una m\xc3\xa1quina que consta de una plataforma m\xc3\xb3vil en la que la persona se extiende y que debe mover contra la resistencia de unos muelles, como si fuese una prensa de piernas pero donde las piernas y el cuerpo permanecen en el mismo plano, tendido en supino. Adem\xc3\xa1s consta de unas correas y una caja con las que poder entrenar encima de la camilla en otros planos y de diversas e infinitas formas. 

El Cadillac, es una m\xc3\xa1quina que consta de una peque\xc3\xb1a plataforma, un poco m\xc3\xa1s grande que una persona a la que se le ha a\xc3\xb1adido una especie de dosel al que a su vez se le a\xc3\xb1aden muelles, correas e incluso un peque\xc3\xb1o trapecio. Es un lujo de m\xc3\xa1quina donde los cuerpos pueden entrenar en un sinf\xc3\xadn de planos, de posiciones, en contra de resistencia o a favor, o simplemente utilizarse como camilla tal cual. 

El Barrel, tal y como su nombre indica, es una m\xc3\xa1quina en forma de medio barril, d\xc3\xb3nde se ejecutan ejercicios de fuerza- resistencia como de estiramientos.

La Chair, es una especie de silla con pedales donde la persona podr\xc3\xa1 disfrutar de una bater\xc3\xada de ejercicios en la que destacan dos aspectos de Pilates por encima de los dem\xc3\xa1s la Disociaci\xc3\xb3n y el Control. Adem\xc3\xa1s si fuese necesario se le podr\xc3\xada dar un matiz de entrenamiento de la fuerza del tren inferior.

El Spine Corrector, es un peque\xc3\xb1o barril donde el cliente se tumba y que obliga a una suave extensi\xc3\xb3n de la columna tor\xc3\xa1cica que aporta un beneficio extraordinario a la apertura de la caja tor\xc3\xa1cica, con todos los beneficios que ello comporta. 

Finalmente el Ped- o- Pull, que no sale en esta grabaci\xc3\xb3n, es un aparato donde el cliente est\xc3\xa1 de pie y ejecuta diversidad de ejercicios con las manos traccionando de muelles de diversas resistencias.

Title: b'Comparaci\xc3\xb3n del Ejercicio Backstroke en Pilates Reformer y Pilates Mat'
Description:
b'- Prof. Nancy Sabo. Ejercicio avanzado de Pilates.
- Pilates: Fortalece las articulaciones. Permite alcanzar la armon\xc3\xada entre el cuerpo y la mente. Corrige las malas posturas. Mejora la agilidad, la coordinaci\xc3\xb3n, el control, la destreza, el equilibrio corporal y la flexibilidad, 
Estimula la circulaci\xc3\xb3n sangu\xc3\xadnea y el retorno venoso. Desarrolla la concentraci\xc3\xb3n. Modela el cuerpo. Tonifica. Sirve para rehabilitar lesiones.
El m\xc3\xa9todo Pilates es una t\xc3\xa9cnica de movimiento muy completa, trabaja el cuerpo en su totalidad. 
Es una combinaci\xc3\xb3n de movimientos basados en t\xc3\xa9cnicas de gimnasia, yoga, ballet y kinesiolog\xc3\xada..
Trabaja los m\xc3\xbasculos de adentro hacia fuera, contrariamente a lo que sucede con la gimnasia tradicional.
Forma cuerpos longil\xc3\xadneos, esbeltos, flexibles y fuertes por dentro.
Oxigena correctamente con la respiraci\xc3\xb3n tor\xc3\xa1xica lateral.
Puede ser practicado por personas de la tercera edad, embarazadas y gente con problemas f\xc3\xadsicos (Patolog\xc3\xadas).
Es un entrenamiento intenso muy utilizado por los bailarines. 
Mantiene en todo momento el control desde el power-house (faja abdominal y lumbar) hacia las extremidades. 
- La t\xc3\xa9cnica de Pilates Mat b\xc3\xa1sicamente es la misma que Pilates en Camas, en mat se trabaja sobre una colchoneta con la fuerza del propio cuerpo, aunque se pueden incorporar elementos (mancuernas, aro magico, bandas el\xc3\xa1sticas, pelotas) mientras que en reformer se utiliza una camilla con un sistema de poleas y resortes de distintas intensidades.
Pilates mat se puede realizar en clases grupales, personalizadas o en tu propio hogar.

- Nota emitida en el programa Todos Los Gimnasios TV, para ver el programa completo de esta semana ingres\xc3\xa1 a: www.todoslosgimnasios.com.ar.

Description:

Minimum Calories For Performance
Here is the quickest rule in the book. If you are getting stronger, and getting results in the gym, you are eating the right amount of calories for your body. Most people are inefficient with their calories. Properly timed calories are most important. The starting guidelines are below, stick with this for a couple weeks, if you aren't getting stronger or gaining a little size, bump your total cals by 200 (keeping the SAME ratio) 

Endomorphs BASE Guidelines: Protein= 1.25 grams per pound of body weight
Carbs= 1.25  gram per pound of body weight
Fat= 0.6 gram per pound of body weight


Carbs Should Be Timed, Mixed
More carbs should be consumed around exercise. About 50% around exercise (these are your fast acting carbs like a waxy maize, dextrose, or sugar), 25% for breakfast (more complex, think oats, sweet potatoes etc) and 25% spread over your remaining meals (veggies, beans, lentils, high fibre carbs)


Steady State vs High Intensity Cardio
Activating, converting or stimulating fast Twitch Muscle Fibres should be the goal of your cardiovascular activity. Because you are gaining muscle and eating enough calories, high intensity cardio would be smart to include. 3x per week, either after exercise, on off days or six hours after exercise. 15-20 minutes. If you feel like dying, its good cardio.

Control Days
For thicker dudes, on their days off, I'd highly recommend low carbing it to make their insulin more sensitive. Remember the simple point that carbs are for energy. Eliminate your carbs from your daily caloric intake (or less than 50 grams) and keep everything else the same.

Heavy Lifting
Remember how we said you are built for more endurance exercise? This means you are poor at activating your fast twitch muscle fibres. Well we want you to be fast and explosive. Think athletic. Myogenic tonus, how firm the muscle feels at rest. Don't chase the pump, you need to build the fast twitch muscle fibres.

Title: b'Build Leg Muscle FAST (hard) - Mix Up Lunge Complex'
Description:
b'WEBSITE:  http://www.synergy-athletics.com STRENGTH MANUAL: http://www.BullStrength.com

Lunges in particular are great for athletes and people looking for that "real world strength."  Life and sports usually include a high amount of unilateral movements. 

The "mix up" lunge complex requires a huge amount of stabilization, leg strength, and leg endurance.
Mix Up Lunge Complex:

   1. Overhead lunges x 5-8
   2. Front bar lunges x 5-8
   3. Zercher lunges x 5-8
   4. Back bar lunges x 5-8

These should all be done in a row without putting the bar down.  You may perform front, side, or reverse lunges.
Primary  Muscles Used:

    * Quads
    * Glutes
    * Shoulders
    * Core
    * Upper back

Want a COMPLETE exercise program to plug the Mix Up Lunges into?  Get on Bull Strength.  http://www.bullstrength.com

Title: b'Get Even Stronger To Get Your "Muscle Up" Routine! (Intermediate)'
Description:
b"This is a routine to work towards your first muscle up. This is a continuation of this routine is http://youtu.be/RWVaWfMOxHw This is the most advanced version so please watch that one and read the video description first before proceeding to watch this one.  

   Okay the changes you will see to this routine will be during the negative muscle up the time has changed to 10 seconds now. Please make sure to really focus on the transition from dip to pull up and slow that down as much as possible. Next will be 10 clap pull ups. Pull all the way up then release your hands for a quick clap then re catch the bar. If you can't do ten clap pull ups then do as many as you can then finish with regular pull ups until you reach ten reps. Next will be 15 straight bar dips. Next 15 explosive knee raises. Then 15 clap push ups. Then here we will do 10 head bangers. Watch this video of how to head bangers http://youtu.be/x6rGpfYckAY Head bangers will help you get use to the position in which your arms will pass through when going for a muscle up which is much different then when performing a standard pull up. Keep the bar in front of you not over.

Je hei\xc3\x9fer die Temperaturen werden, desto mehr machen wir uns Gedanken \xc3\xbcber unsere Strandfigur. Viele unter uns fangen dann mit einem Fettverbrennungs-Training an oder ern\xc3\xa4hren sich bewusster und ges\xc3\xbcnder. Doch oftmals geht das Abnehmen langsamer voran als man sich das w\xc3\xbcnscht. Darum gebe ich Dir heute insgesamt 4 Tips, die Dir helfen den Fettabbau zu beschleunigen.

Tip #1 - Auf die richtige Gr\xc3\xb6\xc3\x9fe der Mahlzeiten achten

Gro\xc3\x9fes Fr\xc3\xbchst\xc3\xbcck. Mittleres Mittagessen, und eine kleinere Portion f\xc3\xbcr das Abendessen. Damit versorgt Du deinen K\xc3\xb6rper genau mit der richtigen Energie-Menge. Morgens braucht den K\xc3\xb6rper sehr viele Kalorien, um in die G\xc3\xa4nge zu kommen, w\xc3\xa4hrend Abends der K\xc3\xb6rper seinen Verbrauch mehr und mehr verringert bis zum Schlafen gehen.

Tip #2 - Passiven Energieverbrauch erh\xc3\xb6hen

Muskeln verbrennen Fett - je mehr Muskeln Du hast, desto schneller ist auch die Fettverbrennung. Darum solltest Du ein regelm\xc3\xa4\xc3\x9figes Muskelaufbau-Training machen, um so nach und nach den Energieverbrauch zu erh\xc3\xb6hen. Frauen aufgepasst!!! Ihr braucht keine Angst haben, eines Tages zu muskul\xc3\xb6s zu sein. Frauen bauen genetisch bedingt sowieso langsamer Muskulatur auf. Und so einen knackigen Po wie Jennifer Lopez bekommt ihr nur durch ein Muskelaufbau-Training.

Tip #3 - Naturbelassene Lebensmittel essen

Vermeide industriell gefertigte Lebensmittel wie Fertiggerichte, Tiefk\xc3\xbchlgerichte, Pasta, Brot usw. und esse statt dessen z.B. einen leckeren Fruchtsalat oder ein selbst gemachtes Bananen-Eis. Dort sind n\xc3\xa4mlich viel mehr Vitamine, Minerale und Enzyme enthalten, die die Fettverbrennung beschleunigen und den Stoffwechsel ankurbeln.

Tip #4 - Kurze und intensive Workouts

Damit kannst Du mit nur 5 Minuten Zeiteinsatz den Fettabbau f\xc3\xbcr die n\xc3\xa4chsten 2 Stunden anregen. Das ist deutlich effektiver als langweilige Ausdauer-Trainings auf dem Cross-Trainer oder dem Laufband.

Mit diesen 4 einfachen Tips kannst Du deine Fettverbrennung richtig auf Hochtouren bringen. Ein flacher Bauch oder eine attraktive Bikini-Figur muss nicht l\xc3\xa4nger nur ein Traum bleiben.

To get the most out of your pullup here's a couple tips for you:

Title: b'KILLER Leg Training - Countdown Sets Alternating Bottom Squats and\nStiff-Leg Deadlifts'
Description:
b'http://www.thebestlegexercises.com - Today I want to introduce you to a powerful and very intense training technique called "countdown alternating sets." 

The goal of this style of training is to "front load" the reps for two exercises...this means getting as much work done up front while you're still relatively fresh, then continuing the sets using decreasing rep ranges to stretch that workload and do more overall reps.

And yes, it may sound confusing when I explain it like that but once you see it in action (and give it a try), you'll see exactly how it works and why it's so challenging and effective.

You're basically squeezing as much work out of your body as possible in a very short period of time and it's INCREDIBLY productive. 

How to do Countdown Alternating Sets 

I'll explain this one using a couple of demo exercises for legs...the bottom-start squat off the rails (also known as an Anderson Squat after legendary strongman Paul Anderson) and stiff-legged deadlifts.

And just so you know up front, you can use this technique with just about ANY exercise combination. I prefer antagonistic muscle pairings like quads and hamstrings, back and chest and biceps and triceps, but you could very easily do non-related exercise pairings as well.

The two exercises I used here are a GREAT combination if you're looking for some seriously efficient leg training. Literally all you need to train everything in your entire lower body is covered in about 4 to 5 minutes of training time.

Start by getting your equipment set up and ready to go. For bottom-start squats, set the rails a little higher than your normal bottom squat position. You'll need a bit higher start position because there is no elastic tension to help you out of the bottom...it's all muscle tension (which is great for the muscles but much harder in terrms of the movement itself).

I'm using this version of the squat for two reasons.

1. Reduced time to start the exercise. Instead of having to get under the bar, unrack it and step back, then do the reps and step forward and rereack it, all I have to do is get under the bar and start the movement. You can absolutely do normal squats if you prefer.

2. Increase muscle tension and strength deveopment out of the bottom of the squat. As I mentioned, starting with zero elastic tension is a lot harder for the squat and it'll help with quad and glute development as well as building strength out of the bottom.

For stiff-legged deadlifts, just get your bar set up right in front of the squat rack. No tricks needed there.

Get under the bar and do 5 reps. For this bottom-start version, I recommend setting the bar down on each rep so that you're starting from a dead stop on each rep.





When you're done, set the bar down and turn around do and 5 reps of the stiff-legged deadlift.

When doing this exercise, your knees should be slightly bent but kept stiff. Keep your core tight and an arch in your lower back. I can see in these pics, I need to work on my flexibility ;). 

I've got 225 lbs on the bar, same as for the bottom-start squats. You should use weights that you could do at least 12 to 15 reps with straight through. I'd actually recommend erring on the side of lighter the first time through. The fatigue catches up to you FAST.





Similar to the bottom-start squats, I recommend setting the bar down on the floor in between reps and starting from a dead stop. I find this allows you to focus on engaging the hamstrings on each rep rather than worrying about coming back up right away. Also, it allows you to reset your back position at the bottom so you don't get excessive rounding. 

When you've done 5 reps of this go DIRECTLY back to the squats for 4 reps.

When you've done 4 reps, go back to SLDL's and do 4 reps.

Then back to squats for 3 reps, then SLDL's for 3 reps. Then 2 reps, then finish with 1 rep.

Then you're done! (and you will be DONE). 

As you can see, even though I made it sound complicated in the beginning, it's actually pretty simple. You'll just bounce back and forth between two exercises, doing fewer and fewer reps. You're basically "chasing fatigue" with this rep scheme, decreasing the reps as you get tired. 

And let me tell you, if you've got the weights about right, you will feel GASSED probably on the 3 rep sets. But because you have in your head that next sets are only 2 reps and 1 rep, you'll keep going and finish it out to the end.

For me, I only needed one round through of this and my legs were cooked. If you needed to, you could potentially do one or two more rounds through of this, but don't blame me if you can't walk up or down a flight of stairs for the next two days (ok, you can still blame me).

Give this combination a try in your next leg workout or try it with other exercises combinations. It's extremely time-efficient and incredibly powerful. 

If you enjoy hard training, you're going to LOVE this technique.'

Title: b'Calisthenics exercises: How to do a chin-up - A guide to your first chin-up ever (HD)'
Description:
b'Subscribe \xe2\x96\xba https://goo.gl/AyP9zk

How to do a chin-up - A guide to your first chin-up ever

I have 25 years of training. I cannot tell you how often I have seen guys who move around pretty impressive weights in the gym but yet cannot do a single chin-up (much less a pull-up). I think that's a pity.

What's the point of training separate muscle groups with huge weights but when a simple exercise, like the chin-up, requires you to use a big part of your body in unison you are not able to.

On the other hand, there are many, many folks out there who sincerely wish to be able to do a chin-up but for whatever reason have not been able to. 

They may not have had the proper instruction, they may have given up too early, or they may have even suffered an injury while trying a chin-up in an unsafe way.

For all these folks who want to get to their first chin-up ever, I created this short and fun guide (really, it was fun making it).

Title: b'Build a Gigantic Back and Arms! | Wendler 5/3/1 Deadlift C4.3'
Description:
b"Ok so it's the finale of Cycle 4 for Wendler 5/3/1 and today was the Deadlift / Upper Back and Biceps session. Loaded up on Driven Sports Craze I was ready to go kill it...

For the 1+ Set for this Cycle I managed to hit 180kg x 2 reps. This is a new Raw PR for me. I felt that going for another rep would of stressed me too much so I gave it a miss. Immediately after I fancied my chances at 190kg but couldn't get it past a couple inches.

Followed up with Boring But Big Squats, moved up 5kg to 90kg x 10 now. These feel like they are really making an impact to my legs already... good things!

For Upper Back assistance, started with Overhand Pull Ups followed by Yate's Rows, Seated Cable Close Rows, Lat Pull Downs and finishing with a few sets of Dumbbell Hammer Curls for the Biceps.

Felt like a pretty good session, the deadlifts took quite a lot out of my hamstrings so I was finding stability with the Yates rows quite difficult but managed to do what I could.

End of another great Cycle. Definitely feel like I am making good progress with this program and looking forward to starting Cycle 5 after my deload week. I am also planning to run another Bench Specific program alongside 5/3/1 on starting Cycle 5 but will talk more about that another day.

Thanks for watching and all the support these past 4 cycles!

Title: b'Alzate della gamba con la palla tra i piedi - Terry Fitness'
Description:
b"Come si eseguono le Alzate della gamba con la palla tra i piedi, esercizio per allenare gli Addominali e le Gambe

Esecuzione delle Alzate della gamba con la palla tra i piedi:

1. Distenditi con la schiena a terra e tieni una palla tra le caviglie

2. Alza le gambe verso l'alto con le ginocchia leggermente flesse

3. Stringi la palla tra le caviglie, controlla il movimento e scendi verso il pavimento senza toccare; mentre scendi porta le gambe verso il lato destro, poi alzale e scendi verso sinistra.

4. Alterna lato destra e sinistro.

Errori comuni nelle Alzate della gamba con la palla tra i piedi:

\xe2\x80\xa2 Distendere le gambe
\xe2\x80\xa2 Inarcare la schiena in fase di discesa delle gambe.

Title: b'Full Body or Split|Which workout is best?'
Description:
b"Full Body workouts work on your entire body to make a great foundation and or frame. 

When you do full body's you train your muscles to a point that is not to failure and optimize your ability to target the same muscle groups 48 hours later. Keeping muscles growing with shorter recovery times.

When you get to a more advanced stage which I say 1 to 2 years down the road then you can start a split because your Frame and foundation would be build from the full body workouts by then and you will have to start targeting or isolating your muscle groups, training them a lot more aggressive on 1 day of the week then moving on to the next muscle the next day and so on and so fourth.

I recommend starting with a full body workout for 1 to 2 years.

Scivation Xtend Review.
If you look around the gym you might notice people with colorful drinks in hand. This is likely an intra-workout supplement, and quite possibly Scivation Xtend since it's so incredibly popular. But is it the best? Let's look at the label.
So here we see that it's supposed to help to build muscle, burn fat, and recover faster. It provides 3500 mgs of l-leucine for increased protein synthesis, a total of 7000 mg's for bcaas, and over 4500 mgs of glutamine, citrulline malate and electrolytes. It also doesn't contain any sugars or carbs. So far it's looking great, let's see what real consumers have been saying about xtend, time for some social proof.
Reported pros
- Faster recovery
- Increased energy
- Increased endurance
- Awesome taste
Reported Cons
- A bit pricey
- Container doesn't last long enough
So far it's looking promising, let's look at the ratings. Here we see that bodybuilding.com has 1862 ratings scoring a rock solid 9. Supplementreviews.com show 17 ratings for the new formula and scores a similar 8.8. This gives us a total of 1879 ratings rounding off at 9.00. That's a great score for that number of ratings. Let's take a look at the active ingredients.
L-Leucine (3500 mgs)
- One of the major uses of L-Leucine is for building muscle mass. 
- This amino acid helps to promote strength and energy while working out.
- Another related benefit of L-leucine is for preventing the damage of muscle tissue in the body. 
- This amino acid helps to keep the body in an anabolic state.
L-Glutamine (2500 mgs)
- After excessive physical exercise, the body may suffer from muscle breakdown. 
- In this condition, the glutamine level in the body is reduced which in return induces the catabolic function of the stress hormone cortisol. 
- Glutamine is essential for blocking cortisol and therefore is known to impart anti-catabolic properties.
- Another major benefit of glutamine is its ability to increase nitrogen retention. 
L-Isoleucine (1750 mgs)
- This promotes the production of hemoglobin thereby strengthening the blood cells to gain maximum energy to repair tissue damage.
- This amino acid also helps  with the production of energy.
- It's also useful for maintaining the required level of nitrogen for the body to remain healthy and fight against certain diseases.
L-Valine (1750 mgs)
- It helps with faster recovery from muscle fatigue and, therefore, helps bodybuilders and athletes to improve and maintain their strength.
- This amino acid also supports the function of various other proteins and amino acids in the body thereby improving the ability of the nervous systems to perform various cognitive functions effectively.
Citrulline Malate (1000 mgs)
- Used by the body to increase plasma levels of the amino acid L-Arginine. 
- Recent studies show that the use of Citrulline Malate effectively raises L-Arginine plasma levels more effectively than taking L-Arginine itself.
- Citrulline Malate may also serve to increase nitrogen production, reduce lactic acid build up, and increase overall atp production.
Final Verdict
Xtend has been a long time favorite for many bodybuilders when it comes to BCAA supplements. The user can expect:
- Increased energy
- Decreased recovery time
- Increased lean muscle mass
However, draw backs to consider are:
- It's a bit pricey
- Tub doesn't last that long

Title: b'How I Ended My Lower Back Pain - Part 10: Leg Magic'
Description:
b'I love exercise machines that make you sore in areas where you're flabby but never get sore.  That tells me I'm exercising muscles that are generally neglected.  The Leg Magic machine ($100 on Amazon.com) is the perfect machine to get to your upper inner-thigh muscles.  What does this have to do with back pain?  

I sincerely believe that the success of my lower back & ab exercise program is due to the fact that I'm hitting more than the obvious muscles.  Clearly bench crunches (video #5 in this series) and the Ab Coaster (video #7) work on the main abdominal muscles you need to strengthen in order to support your lower back.  But your upper thigh muscles are important too.  In video #9, I demonstrate the Gazelle Freestyle, which gives you great upper thigh stretching, and in this video I demo the Leg Magic machine that gets those inner thigh muscles.

The total cost of all the machines I use in my lower back / ab workout was around $1000.  That may sound like a lot to spend, but as exercise machines go, it's really cheap.  You can go to a gym and have access to lots of machines, but the question is, "will you do it 3-5 times each week for the rest of your life?"  Unlikely.  Of course, it's also unlikely that you will use the equipment just because you buy it.

It all gets down to self-discipline, self-motivation and commitment.  This stretching & exercise program works for me, and I'm sharing it in the hopes that it will be helpful to you as well.  Good luck!'

Title: b'Best Squat Stance (SURPRISING ANSWER!)'
Description:
b"Find the best squat for you...and get bigger legs faster!
http://athleanx.com/x/better-results-faster

Determining the best squat stance and width is like finding the Holy Grail.  If you find it, you'll know it!  This is because those that have found their squatting sweet spot are usually the ones that can get the biggest legs fastest and seem to be able to squat more weight than everyone else.

As you'll see in this video however, finding the perfect squat stance width can be challenging.  This is because squatting stance and foot width are largely determined by our anatomy.  The shape of the head and neck of the femur have a large say in whether you should be squatting with a narrow stance or a wide stance.  Furthermore, whether you should be pointing your toes out or toes in on your squat is also determined by the shape of the bones articulating with the hip.

When the head of the femur is longer than normal, your hip joint articulates more comfortably with the leg positioned further away from the body.  This means, those with this type of femur would find squatting wide to be more comfortable than narrow.

Those with an anteverted head of the femur will find that they naturally pigeon toe.  Asking this person to point their toes out during a squat is a recipe for disaster.  Demanding this claiming that it is perfect or best squat form is not advisable here.  

Likewise, someone with a retroverted femoral head would find that squatting with toes straight ahead is extremely challenging and actually damaging to the knee.  The best stance for squats is going to be determined by testing how YOU feel performing some reps in each of the positions.

You can do this on a back squat, sumo squat, front squat or any other squat variation that you are able to perform with good form.  Determine your foot position and ideal foot placement on squats and you'll go a long way to making faster gains from your leg workouts.

For a complete workout program that helps you to train your legs like an athlete, be sure to head to http://athleanx.com to get your ATHLEAN-X athlete endorsed workout program.

For more leg workouts, squat tips and exercises for your lower body and core be sure to subscribe to our channel on youtube at http://youtube.com/user/jdcav24"

 TTS es para TODOS. Nuestro sistema fue creado para adaptarse f\xc3\xa1cilmente a personas de cualquier condici\xc3\xb3n f\xc3\xadsica. TTS es entrenamiento autoregulado. La intensidad y la cantidad de trabajo dependen de vos. En TTS no se cuentan repeticiones, no es lo mismo para todos.

Title: b'Day 47 | Common Mistakes In The Gym: 12-Week Hardcore Daily Video Trainer With Kris Gethin'
Description:
b"Get the entire program FREE here: http://bbcom.me/Q8ENCy

Follow Kris as he takes you and himself through a 12-week transformation. Rest up as Kris talks about common mistakes he sees in the gym and why you should avoid them!

Tips For The Rest Day
Warming Up:
\xe2\x80\xa2 Don't go straight into your working sets, even if you are feeling good or are strapped for time.
\xe2\x80\xa2 Warming up helps get proper blood flow for increased muscle performance, and is good for preventing serious injuries.
Proper Breathing:
\xe2\x80\xa2 Don't hold your breath while lifting!
\xe2\x80\xa2 You need adequate oxygen in your brain and muscles to maintain muscle performance and fight fatigue.
\xe2\x80\xa2 Breathe IN when you are lowering the weight back to the starting position, and breathe OUT when you are lifting the weight.
Heavy Lifting For Women:
\xe2\x80\xa2 Lifting heavy won't make you a bulking beast, ladies.
\xe2\x80\xa2 Lifting heavy increases muscle density, resulting in an increased metabolism and lean muscle.
\xe2\x80\xa2 Women naturally do not put on mass like men do, so don't worry about lifting heavy and pushing yourself!
Carbohydrates:
\xe2\x80\xa2 Never cut them out!
\xe2\x80\xa2 The body needs complex carbohydrates for energy and to keep your metabolism going.
Cardio:
\xe2\x80\xa2 Don't overdo it - a ton of cardio won't mean faster results. It may work in the short term, but in the long term could hurt your metabolism, so be patient and remember that quality is more important than quantity.

Title: b'Massive Back Dead Squats | Wendler 5/3/1 Deadlift C4.1'
Description:
b"Last night it was time to hit up the Deadlifts for it was Cycle 4 Week 1 of Wendler 5/3/1. I decided to mix things up a little and did Boring But Big Squats after my working sets of Deadlifts... this was really challenging but I think it's gunna benefit my Squat in the long run.

For the 5+ Set on Deads I managed 152.5kg x 9 reps and they all felt pretty good. Very happy with how I have progressed with these doing them Raw... I remember last year when I could only manage 1 rep at these kind of weights. 

Assistance was pretty intense... Squats, Pull Ups, Yates Rows, Close Cable Rows, Lat Pull Downs and finishing with Straight Arm Lat Pull Downs as part of a FST-7 Set. 

Really big session. Took a lot out of me... tried to do some Barbell Curls but still can't even do one rep lol. I may need to look into making some kind of support / splint to allow me to do them.

Anywhos... thanks for watching, see ya in the next video = Overhead Press Day.

Title: b'Motiva\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o Kevin Levrone'
Description:
b'Levrone come\xc3\xa7ou a treinar no Gin\xc3\xa1sio do Metro em Linthicum, Maryland.  Durante sua carreira, Kevin conquistou 22 vit\xc3\xb3rias como profissional IFBB, perdendo apenas para Ronnie Coleman e Vince Taylor.
Levrone venceu o Arnold Classic duas vezes (1994 e 1996) e ficou em segundo lugar no Mr. Olympia quatro vezes em uma d\xc3\xa9cada (1992, 1995, 2000 e 2002).
Kevin faz parte do grupo de fisiculturistas injusti\xc3\xa7ados no Mr. Olympia; Flex Wheeler e Shawn Ray s\xc3\xa3o os outros integrantes. Esses atletas competiam em uma \xc3\xa9poca dominada por Dorian Yates e Ronnie Coleman, e em v\xc3\xa1rias ocasi\xc3\xb5es seus segundos lugares foram duramente criticados pelos torcedores e jornalistas.
Kevin Levrone nunca anunciou oficialmente sua aposentadoria. E recentemente disse que ainda pretende vencer o Mr. Olympia.
Em seu Blog pessoal, Kevin, que estava fora de forma, mostrou sua evolu\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o em um treinamento intensivo de 8 semanas. Os resultados s\xc3\xa3o impressionantes.
Recentemente, Kevin Levrone lan\xc3\xa7ou seu pr\xc3\xb3prio suplemento alimentar, que \xc3\xa9 vendido nas principais lojas dos EUA.
Refer\xc3\xaancias: perfectpeople.net / misterolympia.com.ar'

Title: b'Pilates For Beginners - Is Your Posture Giving You Pain?'
Description:
b'http://mypilatesforbeginners.com/ Pilates For Beginners. Id like to talk to you about Pilates; what its done for me and how it could benefit you too if you take it up and practise the exercises regularly.

Put simply, Pilates has banished my pain; the muscle pain I have held in my neck and back for years. The pain that was the result of years of poor posture and not taking proper care of my back.

None of us want to have pain; those that do have it want a way to ease it, and anyone that doesnt have pain (yet) would be wise to take steps to prevent it.

This video discusses why Beginner Pilates can be so effective in reducing some types of postural pain. To learn more about Pilates and how it could help you please follow the link at the top of this page.'

Title: b'Tiener Evangelisatie Activiteiten 2010 Donderdagavond, Highlandgames'
Description:
b'Twitter:
http://twitter.com/zomerwintertea
Facebook:
http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100002412833793
http://zomer-wintertea.hyves.nl/widget/
Het thema van vanavond was ; Stel je voor...... Jij kunt het verschil maken. We begonnen met het zingen van een aantal liederen en daarna was er weer een sketch te zien. Het ging over Roos en Tess die zichzelf eigenlijk wel heel stoer vonden omdat ze allemaal dingen deden die waar zij lol in hadden, maar wat voor anderen helemaal niet leuk waren. Zo gingen ze de bal afpakken van een kind, en een oude oma omver rijden. Totdat ze een stem hoorden en toen beseften dat het niet goed was wat ze deden, gelukkig konden ze het nog terugdraaien! De bezinning ging over de barmhartige Samaritaan, en werden er voorbeelden gegeven over bepaalde situaties die wij kunnen meemaken, en hoe wij dan zouden reageren. Wanneer je op school in de aula iemand alleen ziet zitten, ga je er dan eventjes bijzitten, of loop je dan toch liever verder? Wij kunnen zelf het verschil maken! Maar gelukkig hoeven we het niet alleen te doen en is er Iemand die ons daarbij wil helpen. Na de bezinning gingen we in groepjes naar de ijsbaan toe om daar de avond voort te zetten.
 
Vanavond waren er ongeveer 50 tieners die de uitdaging aangingen tijdens de Highlandgames. Er waren allerlei verschillende spellen te doen ; Spijkerbroekhangen, het meer van Lochness, buikglijden, touwtrekken en vrachtwagen trekken. Het meer van Lochness was wel erg leuk om te doen, (en nog leuker om naar te kijken!) Er was een heel groot "meer" gevuld met water en zeepsop en in het midden was een grote buis. Op de buis moest je zitten en dan moest je proberen je tegenstander in het water te krijgen door elkaar te duwen en slaan met skippy ballen. Er werden verschillende wedstrijdjes gespeeld, en soms zagen we toch dat de meiden er wel iets beter in waren! Jammer jongens, maar jullie konden jezelf bewijzen tijdens het vrachtwagen trekken! De avond werd afgesloten op de ijsbaan waar we nog een keer het themalied hebben gezongen en het Onze Vader hebben gebeden. Al met al was het weer een geslaagde avond en hopen we op een leuk nachtje weg!'

Der Ramadan \xc3\xa4hnelt stark dem intermittent fasting. Bei dieser Art des Fasten wird an einem Tag gegessen am darauffolgenden wird nichts gegessen. Diese Art der Ern\xc3\xa4hrung bietet eine Vielzahl an Vorteilen:

Reduzierung des Blutzuckerspiegel

Reduzierung von entz\xc3\xbcndungsf\xc3\xb6rdernden Prozessen

eine l\xc3\xa4ngere Lebenserwartung

Title: b'Road to 225 Bench'
Description:
b"Song - True Friendship by Tymono

2 months, 2 cycles of Smolov Jr. for Bench, while squatting to 1RM almost every single day.

I do my arch because I feel stronger this way. I dropped it for a while as you can see in the start, but immediately in training when I set up my arch the load feels easier. Back is fine as it doesn't really take a load. It just has a really exaggerated look especially with my small torso. Take a look at the Lillibridge family. They have large arches as well and are among the strongest powerlifters in the world, with over 2000lb totals. Obviously, I'm not them, but it's about specificity of training. If I wanted to improve my pull ups, would it better to do pull up or rows? Pull ups obviously, and this is a similar concept.
